<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="786" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d786">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">761.9411/138</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Navy Department</gloss> to the
                                <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-17">April 17, 1941</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>The following message was received from the Naval Attaché at Ankara this
                        date:</p>
                    <p>[Paraphrase] When explaining the Japanese-Russian pact, the Russian Naval
                        Attaché said that the Russian policy is clear and that it is to allow
                        everyone else to fight while Russia fights with no one.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>